# R5 risky surfaces — a PR touching ANY of these requires both adversarial
# auditors (audit/grok + audit/gatekeeper) to post a success commit status
# before it can merge. The r5-audit-gate workflow enforces this mechanically.
#
# DESIGN for palios-training: this repo IS a public release artifact — every
# recipe / trainer / config / audit verdict / doc is part of what ships publicly,
# so the WHOLE content surface is risky (a bad change = a public-facing defect /
# leaked path / cannot-lie metric). Fail-closed: gate the whole tree rather than
# an allowlist that drifts. For this repo the R5 audit is "verify-claims-against-
# repo" (per conductor 2026-06-17), not a session-exploit repro. One glob/line.
#
# All shipped training artifacts:
recipes/*
trainers/*
configs/*
audit_results/*
proof_of_run/*
# All public-facing docs + the provenance index:
*.md
# CI/gate config itself (self-protecting — a PR weakening the gate is gated):
.github/workflows/*.yml
.github/r5-risky-paths
.gitleaks.toml
